{
  "doc_id": "28562",
  "text": "Hence, several of the existing models (of AGM contractions) were generalized to the case when belief states are represented by belief bases instead of belief sets. Among those we emphasize the ensconcement-based contractions and the brutal base contractions (of belief bases) proposed in [CITATION_1] , which can be seen as adaptations to the case of belief bases of the epistemic entrenchment-based contractions and of the severe withdrawals, respectively. In fact, the definitions of those operations are both based on the concept of ensconcement, which is an adaptation of the concept of epistemic entrenchment relation to the case of belief bases. In the mentioned paper Mary-Anne Williams has also presented a method for constructing an epistemic entrenchment from an ensconcement relation.",
